<item>
            <title>[LU-3293] Could Lustre support direct I/O&#65311;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3293</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I tested the performance with obdfilter-survey, the max performance is 732MB/s;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Result as follow&#65306;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@50:B3:42:00:00:F4 node&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# nobjhi=1 thrhi=2 size=40960 case=disk sh obdfilter-survey&lt;br/&gt;
Tue May  7 15:52:33 CST 2013 Obdfilter-survey for case=disk from 50:B3:42:00:00:F4&lt;br/&gt;
ost  4 sz 167772160K rsz 1024K obj    4 thr    4 write  722.96 [ 143.90, 342.60] rewrite  732.23 [ 155.69, 205.75] read  790.50 [ 125.87, 228.77] &lt;br/&gt;
ost  4 sz 167772160K rsz 1024K obj    4 thr    8 write  712.76 [ 145.78, 193.74] rewrite  714.39 [ 159.78, 196.75] read  940.83 [ 197.79, 258.72] &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tested the performance with dd &#65288;oflag=direct&#65289; on the same devices, the max performance is 1038MB/s;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I want to know if Lustrefs support direct mode?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
